# Changelog entries are always prepended at the top of the CHANGELOG array,
# so parallel feature branches always collide on those same lines. The default
# 3-way merge interleaves the two insertions and produces broken TypeScript.
# `merge=union` keeps BOTH sides' complete entry blocks instead, which stays
# valid because each entry is a self-contained `{ ... },` object.
client/src/features/settings/changelog.ts merge=union
